modules.description: Encodes and decodes timeline-related data types including dates, text, media, slides, eras, and full timelines using JSON encoding. Works with specific types such as date strings, text content, media references, slide structures, and era definitions. Used to serialize and deserialize timeline data for storage or transmission in a structured format.

Provides operations to construct and manipulate structured time-based content, including date formatting, text annotation, media embedding, and slide sequencing. Works with custom types representing dates, textual entries, media objects, slides, eras, and full timelines. Used to build interactive historical narratives with synchronized visual and textual elements.

Constructs timeline elements with precise temporal and visual attributes, including date objects, text blocks, media entries, slides, and eras. Operates on custom types like `date`, `text`, `media`, `slide`, `era`, and `timeline` to build structured historical or event-based narratives. Used to generate interactive timelines with embedded media, captions, and date ranges for web or data visualization applications.

Provides functions to generate and manipulate timeline data structures, including event creation, sorting, and JSON serialization. Works with custom types such as events, timelines, and timestamps. Used to integrate interactive timelines into web applications by exporting structured data.

Encodes, constructs, and manipulates time-based narratives using custom types for dates, text, media, slides, and eras, enabling structured data handling and interactive content creation. Supports JSON serialization and deserialization of timeline elements, allowing for data persistence and exchange. Provides tools for formatting dates, annotating text, embedding media, and sequencing slides to build synchronized historical presentations. Examples include generating a timeline with embedded videos, converting a timeline to JSON for storage, and formatting dates in multiple locales.
